<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3686.4.6>
    bibo:endPage "492" ;
    bibo:issue "4" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "482" ;
    bibo:volume "3686" ;
    dc:creator "Faille, Arnaud; Fresneda, Javier; Bourdeau, Charles" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "Discovery of a new blind ground beetle in western French Pyrenees, and its relevance to the phylogeny of Pyrenean hypogean Trechini" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224019>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224016>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224018>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224017> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224019>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Cave survey of the type locality, the Grotte d’Oxibar inférieure (modified from Laffite, 1967). Location where the new species was found is indicated by a red dot." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224019/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224016>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2 – 4. Geotrechus sarpedon sp. n.; male genitalia. 2 ― aedeagus in lateral view (scale: 0.2 mm); 3 ― detail of the inner sac. 4 ― detail of the humeral group of umbilicate punctures." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224016/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224018>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Phylogram obtained with RAxML of the combined mitochondrial and nuclear data. Blue: Species currently include in the genus Geotrechus, red: Aphaenops sensu stricto, green: Aphaenops (Hydraphaenops), orange: A. (Cerbaphaenops), brown: A. (Simaphaenops) Quéinnec et Ollivier, 2011. Above nodes, bootstrap support values when> 75. See Table 1 for the localities of the specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224018/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.224017>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Map of Pyrenees showing the distribution of Geotrechus sarpedon sp. n. (red circle), A. (Hydraphaenops) vasconicus Jeannel (blue circles) and A. (Hydraphaenops) galani Español (green circles)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/224017/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

